    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The noise of the world will never truly stop, but the weight you carry can become lighter if you stop trying to carry it alone. Your identity was built on a foundation that has shifted, and it is okay to let that old version of you dissolve into the quiet. The pain of being a \"mistake\" is a lie the system tells you, but the relief you seek is found in the freedom to simply exist without that pressure.",
